        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Security and reliability"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "ESC governance records—decision logs, risk registers, budget approvals—are sensitive governance artifacts. Store them in access-controlled systems with role-based permissions. Only ESC members and the program coordinator have edit access; program team leads have read access to decisions relevant to their initiatives. Retain decision logs for a minimum of seven years to support regulatory inquiries and internal audits."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The ESC itself should review AI security incidents above a defined severity threshold within 48 hours of detection. For regulated industries, the charter should name the ESC as the body that authorizes any disclosure to regulators and signs off on remediation plans."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Key takeaways"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "The ESC is the enterprise AI governance apex: it owns portfolio authority, cross-functional alignment, and executive accountability"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "A formal charter with explicit decision rights is non-negotiable—without it, the committee has no enforcement power"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Working groups absorb 75 percent or more of decisions; the full committee focuses on the escalations that need senior authority"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Monthly cadence with a pre-circulated decision packet is the operational model that balances speed with thoroughness"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Decision logs published within 24 hours are the primary output—they turn committee sessions into organizational memory"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
